The paper deals with circuit complexity and the study of non-commutative Unambiguous circuits and Few-Parse-Trees circuits. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of polynomials, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves depth reduction results, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
